<p>Hey there, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/taarsirion" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6879574); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6879574&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1601962175" alt="TaarSirion" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6879574)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/taarsirion" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6879574); return false;">TaarSirion</a></span>. Welcome to the SCP Wiki!</p>
<p>It's great to see you have a fondness for writing and are interested in putting that towards contributing to the wiki and overall becoming an active participant in the community. We could always use more writers. Don't worry if your native language isn't English. We have plenty of resources such as the forums which I'll link later and the <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/chat-guide">#thecritters IRC chat</a> which allows you to get feedback on all aspects from the actual structuring of a narrative up to SPaG. Additionally, since you're German, have you considered also checking out the <a href="http://scp-wiki-de.wikidot.com/">Deutsch Branch</a> in addition to the EN wiki? There might be a lot you can contribute to there too. Also, we're always looking for people to translate articles into other languages so maybe you'll be able to help out with that.</p>
<p>When getting into writing SCPs for the first time, I always suggest you read some of the newer, top-rated articles already on the site. This will help you gauge what the on-site community is interested in currently, and helps people understand the modern standard of writing here. I personally suggest you check out <a href="/scp-5024">SCP-5024</a>. Anyway, here are some more resources that'll help you out around the site:</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">◎&nbsp;Open&nbsp;Resources&nbsp;◎</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">◉&nbsp;Close&nbsp;Resources&nbsp;◉</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content"></div>
<br />
<div style="text-align: left;">
<p>If you're going to try your hand at writing, try out our sandbox. You can make yourself a page here to store your drafts.</p>
<p><a href="http://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/">Sandbox</a></p>
<p>For hashing out concepts, try out the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-89000/help:ideas-and-brainstorming">Ideas and Brainstorming</a> forum. You can run your ideas by the community if you need help refining your concept.</p>
<p>If you have a draft ready, make a thread in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-50864/help:drafts-and-critiques">Drafts and Critiques</a> forum. Remember to check the stickied posts in the relevant thread for guidelines on how best to use each forum. You can also try the IRC chat for real-time feedback.</p>
<p>From site usage to writing tips, the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/guide-hub">Guide Hub</a> contains a wealth of resources geared towards helping members produce successful articles.</p>
<p>The more time you take to familiarize yourself with the SCP style, the drafting process, and the community, the greater your chances are for success!</p>
<p>As far as reading is concerned, you might want to check out our <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/top-rated-pages-this-month">Top Rated New Pages</a>, which will display the most popular, recent articles. It's helpful to keep up with what's being received well by the community.<br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;"></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<p>With that said, I hope your time here is fantastic. :)</p>

