<p>Hello, my name is Jorge (aka Jorgelino), and i finally decided to join the website after having just lurked for quite a while, because i have an idea for my own SCP article and because i want to be a part of this wonderful community. I don't remember when exactly i learned about SCPs but i think it was about 2 years ago, though i'd only read one or two articles back then. A couple of moths ago i discovered the amazing youtube animated series &quot;confinement&quot; by LordBung on a random reddit thread, which spiked my interest in the SCP universe again, making me read a bunch of other articles and truly immerse myself in the lore of this amazing universe.</p>
<p>My intentions with the site are to read articles and be able to upvote/comment on them, perhaps i'll write a few of my own if i have some really cool idea. Right now i feel pretty inspired to put one of these ideas to the test, but i don't think i'll be doing this very frequently.</p>
<p>My hobbies include reading, playing videogames, watching tv series, anime, as well as playing TTRPGs like Dungeons and Dragons and Call of Cthulhu, which i think will be of great help when writing articles, because as i'm already used to writing lore for the homebrew worlds that i GM for my friends.</p>
<p>I don't have many concerns about the site other than just being a little nervous about writing my own article. I don't really mind the criticism as i'm still new and have a lot to learn but it's always a little heartbreaking to see one of your creations fail, so i can't help but worry about how well i'll do.<br />
<strong>EDIT</strong>: Actually, i do have another concern. I am brazilian, but i intend on writing my SCPs in english, though i'd like to also make a version of my creations in portuguese so that my fellow countrymen can appreciate them as well. How would i go about doing that? Is the brazilian page of the SPC foundation a completely separate thing? Would i have to submit a different article to it? Is there a way provide them a translated version of my SCPs, or perhaps even help translate other SCPs?</p>
<p>Oh, and for this month's question, this might sound a bit cheesy but probably the sound of nature. Waking up in the morning and hearing the birds sing and the wind blow on the leaves of the trees is always calming and refreshing. Perks of living in a small rural town i guess.</p>

