<p>Hello! I have been aware of the SCP community for a number of years now, but until a few days ago it had been a long time since I'd checked in. Now that I have plenty of time on my hands (as well as a brain full of creepy, horrifying ideas that may or may not have been explored here already), I am determined to practice my <em>extremely</em> rusty writing skills. I can't think of a better way to do so than to join an active writing community, and the SCP is right up my alley of &quot;weird, creepy sci-fi stuff&quot; (and I mean that as a compliment)!</p>
<p>Anyways, I'm here to write, meet other writers, seek constructive criticism, and offer my opinions and advice where helpful and relevant!</p>
<p>My hobbies and interests include video games (mostly PC games these days), reading, watching TV and movies (I do not have cable or anything like that, so unfortunately I'm not up to date on a lot of shows and recently released movies), discussing just about anything that doesn't involve politics or current events, and, of course, writing!</p>
<p>Most of my concerns about getting started here involve formatting, using the IRC chat, and getting started with writing my first articles and/or tales. I'm using a Samsung smartphone with Android as well as a laptop with Windows 10; if anyone has useful tips or warnings about common bugs for these devices on this platform, please share!</p>
<p>I have a few ideas for SCP articles already forming, but I haven't had the chance to read very many of the already existing ones yet; that said, if there's someone here with an encyclopedic knowledge of SCPs, I would very much like to pick your brain for fresh ideas or new and interesting takes on oldies-but-goodies.</p>
<p>As for sounds that put me in a good mood&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li>Pouring rain</li>
<li>distant thunder</li>
<li>Relaxing music (especially violin and piano, with or without lyrics)</li>
<li>purring cats</li>
<li>the sounds otters make when being fed</li>
<li>pretty much any adorable animal sound</li>
</ul>
<p>Sorry for the long<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">ish</span> intro post! I'm looking forward to getting involved in the community here, and hope to contribute towards a positive and helpful environment for writers of all ability levels and writing styles!</p>

							</div>

								
					
